The paper proposes a model and algorithm for aggregating ranked data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The use of Thurstone's framework and the extension of the BTL model suggest that the paper is likely to be in the area of machine learning and/or artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed algorithm is based on gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning and data analysis, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to the area of data science (cs.DS). The use of statistical analysis and the consideration of accuracy levels of different users suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the area of information theory (cs.IT) and/or social networks (cs.SI).
